oc:kn_59ebca4d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building or debugging stdio MCP servers" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never log or print to stdout in stdio MCP servers — stdout is reserved for the JSON-RPC MCP protocol. Log to stderr instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Stray output on stdout corrupts the JSON-RPC message stream and breaks server communication" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_7fc18728 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before deploying or testing MCP server configuration" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before configuring any MCP server: verify the command URL is accessible, check executable permissions for stdio, validate SSL certs for network transports, and confirm environment variables for auth tokens are set." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Most MCP connection failures stem from missing prerequisites that are easy to verify upfront" .

oc:kn_a845586a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring Python-based stdio MCP servers" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For Python stdio servers, always set PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1 in env. Use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} for relative paths instead of hardcoded absolute paths." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Python buffering can delay or break JSON-RPC message delivery; the plugin root variable ensures portability across installations" .

oc:kn_cbcfbee4 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring SSE, HTTP, or WebSocket MCP servers" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use plain HTTP or WS — always use HTTPS and WSS for network transports. Never hardcode tokens; always use environment variables." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unencrypted connections expose credentials and data; hardcoded tokens leak via version control" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_d10750e6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When MCP server connections fail or behave unexpectedly" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For stdio failures: check command exists and is executable, verify file paths, review claude --debug logs. For SSE/OAuth failures: clear cached tokens, verify OAuth scopes and redirect URLs, re-authenticate. For HTTP 429 errors: implement rate limiting and retry logic." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Systematic troubleshooting by transport type quickly isolates the most common failure modes" .

oc:kn_d1d882b9 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding which MCP server type to configure" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Choose MCP transport based on use case: stdio for local/NPM servers, SSE for hosted cloud services with OAuth, HTTP for REST APIs with token auth, WebSocket for real-time bidirectional communication." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each transport type optimizes for different latency, statefulness, and authentication requirements" .

